  "packageName": "@cubid/wallet-recovery-react",
  "readme": [
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "# @cubid/wallet-recovery-react\n\nReact helpers for Cubid recoverable wallet flows.\n\nUse this package when a React app needs hosted recovery launch or signed-in\nrelease completion. It builds on\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/wallet-recovery`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": ", accepts an explicit bearer token or async token\nprovider, and does not depend on "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/auth-react`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": ".\n\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "```sh\npnpm add @cubid/wallet-recovery-react\n```"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\n## Registry Availability\n\n- npm: supported\n- JSR: not published by policy\n\n## API Reference\n\n- JSON reference: "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`../../docs/reference/api/wallet-recovery-react.json`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n- Package matrix: "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`../../README.md`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "```tsx\nimport {\n  CubidRecoveryLaunchButton,\n  useCubidRecoveryRelease,\n} from \"@cubid/wallet-recovery-react\"\n\nfunction Recovery({ recoverySessionId }: { recoverySessionId: string }) {\n  const release = useCubidRecoveryRelease({\n    baseUrl: \"https://id.cubid.me\",\n    getAccessToken: () => firebaseUser.getIdToken(),\n    recoverySessionId,\n  })\n\n  return (\n    <>\n      <CubidRecoveryLaunchButton recoverySessionId={recoverySessionId} />\n      <button onClick={() => void release.completeRelease()}>\n        Complete recovery\n      </button>\n    </>\n  )\n}\n```"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\n"
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`bundleMaterial`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": " is only returned by the signed-in completion hook. Backend\ndapp credentials should use metadata-only helpers from "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`@cubid/core`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": ".\n\n## Hosted Smoke Status\n\nThe local SDK acceptance harness verifies the mocked app-recoverable-wallet path\nfrom server enrollment to hosted launch and browser completion. Production\nreadiness still requires a hosted smoke against Cubid Identity/Passport and a\nmarked throwaway relying app.\n\n- Hosted smoke strategy:\n  "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`../../docs/engineering/recoverable-wallet-hosted-smoke.md`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "\n\nThis React package intentionally does not expose a recovery-bundle list hook.\nPublic app code must not receive recovery bundles or dapp-user ids that belong\nto other dapps. Apps should use their own app-scoped recovery metadata and\nlaunch hosted Cubid recovery for an exact "
    },
    {
      "kind": "code",
      "text": "`recoveryBundleId`"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "text": "."
    }
  ]
}
